            <h2 class="section-heading">Interview Grooming Tips</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Dress professionally and appropriately.</li>
                <li>Research the company beforehand.</li>
                <li>Practice commonly asked interview questions.</li>
                <li>Be confident and maintain eye contact.</li>
                <li>Arrive on time for the interview.</li>
                <li>Prepare questions to ask the interviewer about the company or role.</li>
                <li>Ensure your resume and portfolio are up-to-date and tailored for the role.</li>
                <li>Be prepared to discuss your strengths and weaknesses honestly.</li>
                <li>Show enthusiasm and a genuine interest in the position.</li>
                <li>Practice your communication skills: clear, concise, and confident answers.</li>
                <li>Follow up with a thank-you note after the interview.</li>
